{
  "texts": [
    "Datasets could be divided into further categories historical, recent, or live-streaming.",
    "The time also affects legal obligations (e.g., updated regulations), context relevance (macroeconomic conditions), and any potential dataset drift over time (e.g., new financial terminology, products, services).",
    "\"Why would the data/annotations be used?\"",
    "In finance, the motivations range from legal compliance (meeting regulatory disclosure requirements) to investor relations (transparency for shareholders) or internal risk management (spotting financial misconduct).",
    "Data often enables specific downstream applications-like building credit-scoring models or automating customer support."
  ]
}